what is interface?
Interface is something which helps 2 system to interact with each other, without one system
has to know the details of other.

Or in simple term I can say,It helps to achieve abstraction


How to define the interface?
----------------------------
Interface declaration consist of
- Modifiers
- "Interface" Keyword
- Interface Name
- Comma separated list of parent interfaces

public(Modifiers)interface Bird(Interface Name){
  public void fly();
}
- only public and Default Modifiers are allowed (Protected and private are not allowed)

interface Bird{
  public void fly();
}
--------------
Comma separated list of parent interfaces(It can extend from the class)

public interface NonFlyingBirds extends Bird, LivingThings{
  public void canRun();
}

-----------------

1. Abstraction:
   Using interface, we can achieve full abstraction means, we can define WHAT class must do
   but not HOW it will do

   public interface Bird{
   public void fly(); // it is just a signature
  }



